french gdp should rise 2.3 pct in 1988 - ministri french gross domest product should grow by 2.3 pct in 1988 after two pct growth thi year and 2.1 pct in 1986 , the financ ministri said . the latest forecast , prepar by the nation account and budget commiss , assum an exchang rate of 6.20 franc to the dollar thi year and next and an averag oil import price rise to 18.9 dlr a barrel next year from 17.4 dlr thi year and 14.7 in 1986. the commiss , head by financ minist edouard balladur , forecast a fall in consum price inflat to two pct year-on-year at end-1988 from 2.4 pct at end 1987 and 2.1 pct last year . in annual averag term inflat would fall to two pct in 1988 from 2.5 pct thi year and 2.7 pct last year , it said . trade should show a one billion franc annual surplu thi year and next after last year 's 0.5 billion surplu , it ad . employ should rise by 0.1 pct a year over the next two year while the state budget deficit should be cut to 2.2 pct of gdp in 1988 from 2.6 pct thi year and 2.9 pct in 1986. other forecast prepar by the commiss indic a 1.8 pct 1988 rise in household purchas power , up from 1.1 pct thi year but less than last year 's 2.9 pct , and a 1.6 pct rise in household consumpt , compar with thi year 's 1.5 pct and last year 's 2.9 pct . busi invest is forecast to rise four pct a year thi year and next after 3.7 pct last year , with privat sector product invest rise 4.9 pct in 1988 after a six pct rise thi year and 5.5 pct in 1986. the ministri said updat forecast would be prepar befor the autumn to serv as the basi for the 1988 budget , which the govern is now prepar for present in septemb .